text: Martine Zuiderwijk (born February 11, 1984 in Naaldwijk) is a Dutch former figure skater. She is a four-time Dutch national silver medalist and qualified to the free skate at two ISU Championships – the 2001 World Junior Championships in Sofia, Bulgaria, and 2006 European Championships in Lyon, France.
